Targeted Advertising in Virginia, Colorado, Connecticut, Utah, Texas, Oregon, Nevada, Delaware, Iowa, New Hampshire, New Jersey, Nebraska and Montana
EasyVFR 4 app Background location services
During and after a flight, users can analyze their own flight by extracting the stored location data to their logbook and by visualizing their flight track on the EasyVFR 4 map.
In order to keep track of the user's position when the EasyVFR 4 app is in the background, the operating system background location services are needed to keep track of the flight. The user has to enable this manually, opt-in-based. When background location is used, notification is always visible in the operating systems notification center.
Background location is only used in specific situations when all of the following conditions are met:
- Use of background location services is enabled within the EasyVFR 4 app: EasyVFR 4 menu -> System;
- The user has given permission in the OS settings for EasyVFR 4 to use Background location;
- The EasyVFR 4 app is alive in the background;
- The user has enabled flight mode during that session when the app was in the foreground.
No data will be shared with 3rd parties.
This processing constitutes:
a Sharing in California
SafeSky
When the user enables one or more SafeSky options within the EasyVFR app, the app will utilize the SafeSky API to share the user's location, and aircraft profile with SafeSky, as well as receive information on surrounding traffic, as specified by the user's settings within the EasyVFR 4 app. By doing so, the user agrees to be bound by the SafeSky SRL Terms and Conditions and Legal Notice. (Terms and Conditions: https://easyvfr4.aero/safesky-terms-and-conditions/, Legal Notice: https://www.safesky.app/en/mentions-legales)
This processing constitutes:
a Sharing in California
